# Add A Folder to Github Repo
## The Simple & Easy Way: 

**The Drag & Drop Method.**
First, Create or locate the folder on your computer. For example, your Desktop or in Documents.
In the repo you're adding to, select Add File, select Upload File, and then drag the folder from computer (ex Desktop) to the Upload File Section.

*Another option is to upload the folderâ€“ select Choose Your Files, Select the file, then click Upload.

Add a message & description *optional, then click the Commit Changes button. Done. 



